resulting from the use of the company’s products and solu- tions (avoided emissions) helps convey a full picture of the company’s contribution to global decarbonization.

The term “Customer Avoided Emissions” refers to the “posi- tive” impact determined by comparing the GHG emissions of two different solutions or scenarios. Avoided emissions are emissions that are saved or avoided during the customer use phase from the use of our products or financing compared to a baseline (reference scenario).

